      <section eId="sec_20_3_294">
        <num>20-3-294</num>
        <content>
          <p>The corporation is authorized to publish in print or electronically annually, or at more or less frequent intervals determined by the board of directors, an operations report covering the activities of the corporation, including, without limitation, a reporting of revenues and expenditures of the corporation and a statement of the financial condition of the corporation and to furnish copies of such report to the Governor and members of the General Assembly and to other public and private persons and agencies as it may deem appropriate. If operations reports are published on an annual basis, the corporation is authorized to publish them in print or electronically on a state fiscal year, federal fiscal year, or calendar year basis.</p>
